Effect of Ant Species Populations on Presence of Asain Needle Ant

newdf=read.csv("/Users/Casey Lang/Downloads/Ant_Species_Monitoring.csv")
    newdf=newdf%>% select(!Plot_ID)#removes the plot ID from the data
    newdf=newdf[complete.cases(newdf),]#removes rows that contain NAs
    antdf=newdf%>%mutate(asain_needle_ant=as.factor(ifelse(B..chinensis>0,'Yes','No')))#changing asain needle ant variable to binary response
    antdf=antdf%>%select(!B..chinensis)#removing leftover asain needle ant variable
    antdf=antdf%>%select(!Location)#removing location variable
    antdf=antdf%>%select(!..Collection_Date)#removing collection date variable
    antdf
antdf %>%dplyr::count(asain_needle_ant) %>%mutate(Prop=prop.table(n))%>%group_by(asain_needle_ant)#proportion table of entries with and without asain needle ants

Random Forest

antdf<-antdf %>%mutate(ID=row_number())#Creating ID variable to later split dataset
    set.seed(500)#setting seed so result is replicable
    sensitivity_vec=c()
    specificity_vec=c()
    accuracy_vec=c()
    aoc_vec=c()
    for(k in 1:100){#repeat 100 times
    train_dat<-antdf %>%slice_sample(prop=0.80)#training data
    test_dat<-antdf %>%anti_join(train_dat,by="ID")#test data
    train_dat<-train_dat %>%select(!c(ID))#removing ID variable so it is not used in the model
    test_dat<-test_dat %>%select(!c(ID))#same as above
    
    random_forest_fit<-randomForest(asain_needle_ant~.,data = train_dat,ntree=500)#creating random forest (500 decision trees)
    pred_rf<-predict(random_forest_fit,newdata = test_dat, type = "prob")#probabitlties
    test_dat<-test_dat %>%mutate(asain_needle_ant=recode(asain_needle_ant, "Yes"="1","No"="0"))#reformatting variable to work for statistics calculations
    sensitivity_vec[k]=InformationValue::sensitivity(actuals = test_dat$asain_needle_ant,predictedScores = pred_rf[,2])#sensitivity calculation
    specificity_vec[k]=InformationValue::specificity(actuals = test_dat$asain_needle_ant,predictedScores = pred_rf[,2])#specificity calculation
    confmat = InformationValue::confusionMatrix(actuals = test_dat$asain_needle_ant,predictedScores = pred_rf[,2])#saving confusion matrix to later calculate accuracy
    accuracy_vec[k]=((confmat[1,1]+confmat[2,2])/(confmat[1,1]+confmat[1,2]+confmat[2,1]+confmat[2,2]))#accuracy calculation
    
    varImpPlot(random_forest_fit)#plot of importance of variables in the random forest
    }
print("Sensitivity Mean and Standard Deviation:")
[1] "Sensitivity Mean and Standard Deviation:"
mean(sensitivity_vec);sd(sensitivity_vec)
[1] 0.7199782
    [1] 0.1709524
print("Specificity Mean and Standard Deviation:")
[1] "Specificity Mean and Standard Deviation:"
mean(specificity_vec);sd(specificity_vec)
[1] 0.8448649
    [1] 0.1059434
print("Accuracy Mean and Standard Deviation:")
[1] "Accuracy Mean and Standard Deviation:"
mean(accuracy_vec);sd(accuracy_vec)
[1] 0.7916667
    [1] 0.07711559
